
[1]shivering

   SHIV'ERING, ppr.

   1. Breaking or dashing into small pieces.

   2. Quaking; trembling; shaking, as with cold or fear.

   SHIV'ERING, n.

   1. The act of breaking or dashing to pieces; division; severance.

   2. A trembling; a shaking with cold or fear.
